-1 NEWBIE~

Welcome to Magma.  If you are an experienced player of Duris, Basternae,
Basternae II, Toril, or similar muds, you can probably skip over this greeting
since most of the commands are similar to what you are used to.

If this is your first time on this mud, we'd like you to spend a moment or
two reading this so you become accustomed to our game.

First we'll start with a warning: This is a PKILL mud.  You can and will be
attacked by other players.  The objective of this game is to kill those on
the other side of the racewars, but there are those on your own side who
will prey on you if you are weaker than them.  Races on the evil side of the
racewars are especially guilty of this type of play.  Use your wits (and the
"flee" command) to escape and learn the game.  

Secondly, read "HELP STORY".  It will give you some background information
on the theme of this MUD.

Your character will start as a level one of whatever class you chose in a
hometown assigned to your race type.  Look over your starting equipment using
the "equipment" and "inventory" commands.  Explore your hometown a bit,
get used to the combat and spell system, and feel free to "petition" any
questions you might have.

"HELP INDEX" will provide you a jumping grounds to various other topics of
interest.  Magma is a complex mud, but once you get used to our style you'll
see that playing here can be a very rewarding experience.

Thanks and have fun,
The Magma Administrative Staff
~
 
