0 'BAREHANDED FIGHTING'~
Applied Skill
     All classes

This skill represents the proficiency of the character to fight without
wielding weapons.  The higher the level of this skill, the more likely the
character is to hit and cause damage.
~

0 BARKSKIN~
Spell

Syntax:         cast 'barkskin' <target>
Area of Effect: Single target, Touch
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependant on proficiency of caster
Type of Spell:  Enchantment

This spell causes the skin of the target to gain the hardness of bark.
It improves the target's armor class considerably.
~

0 BASH~
Applied skill
     
Syntax:     bash <target>
Aggressive: yes

Bashing is a skill used to knock another player or creature down.  It is most
effective when the person trying to bash is wearing a shield.  Bashing is
a very level dependant skill.  For example:  A level 50 player will hit bash
a lot more frequently than a level 1 player.  Missing a bash will send you
toppling to the ground where you will take extra damage.

Size does matter!  A basher can only bash opponents of the same, one size, or
two sizes smaller.

Note: Paladins and Anti-Paladins can bash effectively without a shield.

SEE ALSO: BODYSLAM, SIZE
~

0 'BATTERING STONESTORM'~
Spell

Syntax:         cast 'battering stonestorm' <target exit>
Area of Effect: Single exit, In-Room
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Instant
Type of Spell:  Invokation

The spell conjures up a magical hail of rocks and stones that are thrown
with great force into a door or blocked exit, attempting to break through
it.  It works in much the same way as the DOORBASH ability.

See also: DOORBASH
~

0 'BATTLE ECSTASY'~
Spell

Syntax:         cast 'battle ecstasy'
Area of Effect: Self
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Short
Type of Spell:  Enchantment

This spell heals the anti-paladin as his group members attack and do
damage to the enemy.  A small percentage of the damage that his party
members do is given to the anti-paladin as health.  This spell will
allow the anti-paladin to go temporarily over his maximum amount of
hit points, but only up to a certain point before he can get no more
benefit from it's effects.
~

0 BEARSTRENGTH~
Spell

Syntax:         cast 'bearstrength' <target>
Area of Effect: Single target, Touch
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     No
Duration:       Dependent on proficiency of caster
Type of spell:  Animal

This spell increases the target's strength, while slightly decreasing
the target's dexterity.  Because of the spell's detrimental effects,
the target will save against it.  Thus, if the target wants to be the
recipient (and lose any chance of a successful sv_spell roll), he should
"consent" to the caster.

See also:  MOUSESTRENGTH, ELEPHANTSTRENGTH, CONSENT
~

0 BERSERK~
Applied Skill

Syntax:     berserk
Aggressive: no

Berserk represents a massive adrenaline rush and an almost mindless rage
and need to kill.  Berserking causes a person to ignore his personal safety
and that of his friends in his lust for blood.

When berserked, the strength and constitution of the player go up, but
dexterity, agility, intelligence, and wisdom all drop.  The player will do
more damage and have more health, but will be easier to hit as well.  When
the effect wears off, the player will return to his normal stats.  If the
drop in hit points because of the player's constitution takes his total to
less than 0, he will die.

You cannot cast spells, flee, or perform many other actions while berserked.
While berserk, you may attack friends because of the blinding rage you are
engulfed in.

You can attempt to start/stop a berserk rage by typing 'berserk'.  Your level
and skill will determine the success of your attempt.
~

