0 'CAULDRON OF REBIRTH'~
Spell

Syntax:         cast 'cauldron of rebirth' <corpse>
Area of Effect: Single corpse, requires consent
Aggressive:     No
Cumulative:     N/A
Duration:       Instant
Type of spell:  Necromancy

This spell will restore life to a corpse, negating most of the
experience lost by the death, in the same manner as the "resurrect"
spell.  However, this spell has a greater chance of failure.

The power of this spell takes a toll on both the druid and the target
and both are exhausted by the procedure.

This spell is not without risks.  If the person being resurrected has
low constitution, the strain of being resurrected may be too great, in
which case the spell may fail, and the corpse will be incapable of
being restored to life.  If this spell fails to work on a corpse, the
corpse may not be resurrected by any other means, either.  Basically,
if a target fails a resurrection or cauldron spell, it cannot be ressed
later.

You must have the target's consent before performing a cauldron of
rebirth or the spell will fail.
~

