0 CONSTRUCT12~

Costs
=====

Submission Fee:                 500
A basic hall:                   7,000
Golem:                          4,500
Additional room:                1,000
Inn:                              750
Fountain:                         500
Holy/Unholy Fountain:           1,750
Shop                            2,000
Healing room:                   3,500
Teleporter:                    10,000 (first)
                               50,000 (second)

Payment must be made in platinum on the same day the guildhall is added
to the map.  It must be made by hand by one of the guild leaders.  

A submission fee must be paid each time a guildhall is sent in.  This
means if you send in a hall, decide you need to change something, you will
be fined an additional 500 platinum.

The inn, shop, and healing rooms are NOT additional rooms.  They must be
placed in existing rooms.  So, for example, you can't buy a basic
guildhall, an inn, a shop, and a healing room and have 8 rooms.  You would
buy the basic hall 3 rooms if you wanted 8 rooms total.  You can place the
inn, shop, and healing room in those 5 basic rooms, however.

Bulliten boards are free.

Teleporters allow instantaneous transportation from a guild hall to a
'friendly' city's inn.  Teleporters are one-way from the guild hall to
the inn.

When purchasing a teleporter for a guild hall, you must choose the
'friendly' city destination.  Friendly cities are those which are the
hometowns of a race on your side of the racewars.  So, a goodie guild
could install a teleporter that leads to the inn in Paranel, or an evil
guild could install a teleporter to the Bloodrock inn.

The guild's first teleporter costs 10,000 platinum.  The second costs
50,000 platinum.  No guild can have more than 2 teleporters.  The two
teleporters do not have to have the same destination.

NOTE: The costs are for the guild as a whole, not per guildhall.  So if
you had two guildhalls, and wanted a teleporter in each one, the cost
would be 60,000 platinum for both teleporters, and you would use up your
maximum of 2 teleporters.

Once added, teleporters are permanent.  They cannot be removed and the
destination cannot be changed.

Stables are not allowed.

Guild chests are buggy currrently, and cannot be purchased.

You may NOT modify an existing guild.  You can replace it (at full costs),
but you will get no credit for the existing hall.

Information you must submit when you send the guildhall in:
===========================================================
Location on the map where you want it linked.
Detailed breakdown of costs.
Room vnum of the inn.  You don't have to do anything in DE to create the inn.
The inn is part of the mud code, and is added by the Guildhall admin.
Mob vnums of the golems.
Room vnum where the guild bulliten board should be located.
~

