-1 ILLUSIONIST~

Masters of deception, Illusionists conjure phantasms in order to distort
perception.  The Illusionst relies on non-existance to sway beliefs and
common sense of those who view the magical illusion.  What is reality?
Entities that lack intelligence are much more susceptible to the magical
effects of an Illusion.  Creatures like Ogres and Centaurs will undoubtably
lack the cognizance to see an Illusion for what it is.

Illusionsts are also able to cast other sorts of magical spells since the
Illusionist is also a practicitioner of Magic.  Yet, the Illusionist uses
non-illusion spells to augment their own spells.

Very powerful Illusionists are capable of mixing illusion with reality to
provide an effect that does possess real aspects.  These powerful spells are
also capable of drawing creatures from the Plane of Shadow for short periods
of time.  These Shadow creatures can cause devestating results to the person
who is their chosen victim.  The culmination of reality with illusion gives
powerful Illusionists a vast arsenal.

Important Attributes: Intelligence

Races: Human, Gnome, Rakshasa

Equipment: Illusionists are spellcasters and are very limited in their use
           of weapons and armor.  They have an unsurpassed ability to use
           magical objects such as staves, wands, and scrolls.


