0 PLANE PLANES~

From the journals of Lord Gorinae, the Planeswalker...

There are many planes of existance on which the creatures of the multi-verse
live.  Many know only of the "True Prime", the land of Magma itself.
Some narrowminded people think of this as our planet alone, but this is not
necessarily true.  The sun, other planetary systems, the stars... all reside
in the True Prime.

The other planes are completely different realms of existence.  They do not
touch our True Prime except by magical means.  These different planes are
accessible through many different spells such as 'plane shift', 'gate', and
the like.  Some creatures seem to have an innate ability to shift themselves
from one plane to another.  

To visualize the layout of the major planes of existence, think of the Astral
as a large diamond or sphere.  Along the equator of this sphere are the
Elemental Planes, spaced out equally.  The "opposing" elements are across
from one another (earth to air, fire to water).  Between these Elemental
Planes are the Paraelemental Planes, where two Elemental Planes intersect.

At the top of this sphere, there's the Positive Elemental Plane, and it's
opposite the Negative resides at the bottom.

Then, to top it all off, each of the Elemental Planes interacts with the
Positive and Negative, just as they interact with each other.  This creates
the Quasielemental Planes.

In theory, there could be an infinite amount of Elemental-related planes,
each caused by the lack of true "borders" between each of them.  The
Paraelemental Planes should interact with the Positive and Negative, and so
on.  This theory hasn't been proven by any explorers that I am familar with.

The Ethereal seems to exist everywhere and nowhere.  It's the realm of the
Demi-Planes, islands of matter in the Deep Ethereal that act much like the
True Prime in many cases.  Notable examples of this phenomenon are the
Demi-Plane of Dreams, the Demi-Plane of Shadows, and the Demi-Plane of Dread.  

Planes that are most commonly known are:

Astral - a dull silver expanse that seems to serve as a nexus for portals to
         other planes. 
Ethereal - another misty realm, though this one is full of color.  Split up
           into the Border Ethereal and the Deep Ethereal.

The Elemental Planes (sometimes called the Inner Planes) - these are the
places where the elementalist mages draw their power.

               Fire        Water       Earth       Air

The Positive and Negative Energy Planes - places of almost pure energy
of lack thereof.  The Positive is a place of radiance, where the
power can burn out a traveler in an instant.  The Negative is the
opposite, a place of cold and void, where the spirit is sucked from
the soul.

The Paraelemental Planes - where two adjacent Elemental planes touch.
        Magma (Fire + Earth)                  Smoke (Fire + Air)
        Ooze (Earth + Water)                  Ice (Air + Water)

The Quasielemental Planes - where a Elemental Plane touches the
Positive and Negative.
        Lightning (Air + Positive)            Vacuum (Air + Negative)            
        Mineral (Earth + Positive)            Dust (Earth + Negative)
        Steam (Water + Positive)              Salt (Water + Negative)
        Radiance (Fire + Positive)            Ash (Fire + Negative)

The True Prime may be dangerous to some, but these other planes of
existance are very deadly and should only be attempted by those of great
skill and mental fortitude.

See Also: ZONES, CREDITS
~

