0 SIZES SIZE~

Every creature on Magma has a size classification.  This size is used
for certain skills, such as bash and springleap.  These skills have
restrictions on the sizes of creatures they can be used on relative to
the size of the player issuing the command.

For example, a player can only bash a creature that is his own size, up
to two sizes larger, or down to two sizes smaller.

In addition to the restrictions, there may be penalties for attempting
to use skills on races that aren't the same size as you.  You can bash
something two size classes smaller, but you'll have a harder time doing
it.

+----------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+
| Size           | Example Races                                             |
+----------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+
| tiny           | worms, rats, bats                                         |
| small          | halfling, gnome, goblin                                   | 
| small-medium   | grey elf, drow elf, mountain dwarf, duergar dwarf         | 
| medium         | human, rakshasa, half-elf, flind, orc, githyanki,         |
|                | githzerai, thri-kreen, aquatic elf                        |
| medium-large   | barbarian, minotaur                                       |
| large          | centaur, troll                                            |
| huge           | ogre                                                      |
| giant          | giant                                                     |
| titanic        | hydra                                                     |
| gargantuan     | dragon, devil                                             |
+----------------+-----------------------------------------------------------+

Please keep in mind the sizes are not simply based on how tall or heavy a
race is.  Other factors such as the strength and physique of the creature
play a part in what size a creature is.  

However, and we can't stress this enough, one of the most important factors
we used was game balance, especially where racewars are considered.  Let's
look at an example:

The ogre is arguably the best warrior class for players on the evil side
of the racewars.  As a huge creature, it can only bash down to medium-large
level, which means it can bash centaurs and barbarians for the most part.
Even reduced, the ogre can only bash medium, which still means most of the
goodie caster races are immune.

This means that race/class combinations that weren't used on Basternae 1
as much are more valuable on Magma.  A duergar warrior, for example,
would have no troubles bashing most of the goodie caster races.  Human and
orc paladins/anti-paladins may not be able to do the damage of the warriors
of a bigger race, but they can keep casters on the ground easier.  It's a
trade-off.

Also notice that some mobs can be larger or smaller than an "average"
creature of that race.  The "enlarge" and "reduce" spells also can affect
a creature's size.
~

